      "value": "<p><strong>Boon</strong>: 3 Armour Points</p><p><strong>Bane</strong>: Forced flee</p><p><strong>Trigger</strong>: Failed Cool Test</p><p><strong>Description</strong>: This mail coat seems to be polished to an almost impossibly bright sheen. It provides 3 APs of protection to the Body and Arms.</p><p>Each time this cursed mail absorbs damage from a blow, the wearer must make a Cool Test. This is a <strong>Very Easy (+60) Cool</strong> Test for the first blow but increases by one step of difficulty for each subsequent blow: an <strong>Easy (+40) Cool</strong> Test for the second, an <strong>Average (+20) Cool</strong> Test for the third, and so on.</p><p>If the wearer fails a Cool Test, they must break from combat and flee until they pass a <strong>Challenging (+0) Willpower</strong> Test. The coat provides 0 APs to any damage taken while fleeing, which may lead to a cowardâ€™s end.</p>"
